Chriſtian Faith is a firm, eſtabliſhed, and an infallible Faith, becauſe it is grounded upon a Rock, againſt which the gates of Hell ſhall not prevail, Matth. 16. v. 18. This Faith is firmly eſtabliſhed by ſuch Authority of God and his Church, that he that will not own the Authority, is as a Heathen and a Publican; God hath declared him ſo;
                  Mat. 18. 17. and what the Church binds on Earth, God binds in Heaven. This Church and Faith is firmly eſtabliſht, becauſe our Saviour hath promiſed, That the Holy Ghoſt, the Spirit of Truth ſhould teach the Believers all Truth, remain with them for ever, ſhew
                  John 14. 16. them things to come to be believed, and ſhould cauſe the Believers to remember all things which Chriſt had already taught, which you read in John 14. and 16. chap.
